  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Erectile dysfunction (ED) is defined as the inability to achieve or maintain an erection
      sufficient for satisfactory sexual performance. An ideal treatment option should be effective
      and reliable, have minimal side effects, be simple to use and affordable. The aim of this
      study was to investigate safety, tolerability and efficacy of vardenafil following a flexible
      dose treatment schedule in subjects with varying aetiology.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
